#Written by Hoa Trinh on 12/18/2017
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#OBJECTIVE:
In this directory you will create:
PDB file with only 2 types of atoms: CA and CB

**********************************************************************************

#STEPS:

1) Command Line

                   ./step1.csh  name

name: name of protein 

Example:                ./step1.csh ci2

2) copy the outputs, i.e, the pdb file and the native map to the directory "2.Topology"

***********************************************************************************

#NOTES:

1) The input files:

	0.Cheungcode.Hoa/Multi_Steps/1.CACB/name.pdb
        0.Cheungcode.Hoa/Multi_Steps/1.CACB/name.pdb.CBcrd
	0.Cheungcode.Hoa/Multi_Steps/1.CACB/name.num

2) The needed scripts and other files:

	a) cpp code

		countline.cpp						  : calculates the number of native pairs
	        pdb.cpp						          : produce pdb file of only CAs and CBs

	b) shell scripts 
		
		step1.csh						  : the main script


	c) header file

		common.header                                             : template, will be updated in step1.csh
		common.h                                                  : updated header file

3) The output files:

	name.ab.pdb							  : pdb file of only CAs and CBs

